                        <p>With mass production and little technique now a calling card of the eyewear industry, Lewis
                            Fredericks instead pays tribute to the rich history of eyewear’s past, through recycling the
                            traditionally used material of horn, polarised lenses and expert hand craftsmanship.</p>
                        <h3 class="heading">Ethical</h3>
                        <p>Lewis Fredericks Eyewear offers time-honoured silhouettes fashioned from waste horn, the
                            previously discarded by-product of domesticated Buffalo, Ox and Ram.</p>
                    </div>
